There are multiple approaches to using the Model Context Protocol (MCP) with Salesforce Commerce Cloud depending on your use case.

For developer tasks, Salesforce provides an official B2C DX MCP server, which is part of the B2C Developer Toolkit. It supports cartridge deployment, Managed Runtime (MRT) operations, and SCAPI integration [1][2]. You can configure it in your MCP client using:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "b2c-dx-mcp": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@salesforce/b2c-dx-mcp@latest", "--allow-non-ga-tools"]
    }
  }
}
```

A separate B2C Commerce MCP Shopper Service is available as a pilot for agentic shopper experiences, such as product search and cart management, using HTTP-based JSON RPC [3]. Additionally, community-developed options exist, such as the commercecloud-mcp-server for OCAPI-based interactions [4] and Vinkius's enterprise-focused MCP solution [5].
